---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Outreach" description="Public engagement: lectures, debates, the PACT School Tour, media appearances, and the Hannah Arendt Institute.">

  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Outreach</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        I believe research should serve the broader society. Through public lectures, school visits, media engagement, 
        and my work with the Hannah Arendt Institute, I try to make academic knowledge about polarisation and democracy 
        accessible and actionable.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PACT SCHOOL TOUR -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section__label">PACT School Tour</p>
      <div style="max-width: 680px;">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">VUB PACT School Tour</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          As part of the <a href="https://www.vub.be/nl/over-de-vub/publieksprogramma/pact-caroline-pauwels-academy-critical-thinking" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Caroline Pauwels Academy of Critical Thinking (PACT)</a>, 
          I give guest lectures at secondary schools across Flanders and Brussels on polarisation, democracy, and critical thinking.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          The PACT School Tour brings academic researchers into classrooms to engage students with the big questions of our time. 
          My sessions focus on helping young people understand what polarisation is, how it affects democracy, 
          and how they can think critically about the divisions they encounter in their own lives.
        </p>
        <a href="https://www.vub.be/nl/nieuws/vub-pact-school-tour-caroline-pauwels-atheneum-polarisatie" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="section__more">Read more about the PACT School Tour →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HANNAH ARENDT INSTITUTE -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section__label">Hannah Arendt Institute</p>
      <div style="max-width: 680px;">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Academic member, Hannah Arendt Instituut</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          The <a href="https://hannah-arendt.institute/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hannah Arendt Institute</a> for diversity, urbanity, and citizenship is a collaboration between VUB and UAntwerpen, 
          based in Mechelen. It bridges scientific knowledge about citizenship, urban life, and diversity with the practices 
          and insights of policymakers, organisations, and citizens.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.75;">
          As an academic member, I contribute to the institute's work on polarisation and democratic resilience, 
          including the <strong style="font-weight: 500;">PolarProf</strong> programme that supports local governments in addressing harmful polarisation, 
          disinformation, and hate speech.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PUBLIC APPEARANCES -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section__label">Public lectures &amp; debates</p>
      <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        I have given 10+ presentations to the broader public in schools, public events, and public debates. 
        A selection of my public engagement activities:
      </p>

      <div class="pub-item">
        <div>
          <p class="pub-title">PACT School Tour: guest lectures on polarisation</p>
          <p class="pub-authors">Secondary schools across Flanders and Brussels</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-meta"><p class="pub-year">2025–present</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="pub-item">
        <div>
          <p class="pub-title">Public lectures and debates via Hannah Arendt Institute</p>
          <p class="pub-authors">Various venues, Mechelen and beyond</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-meta"><p class="pub-year">2022–present</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="pub-item">
        <div>
          <p class="pub-title">EDMO BELUX Lunch Lecture on polarisation</p>
          <p class="pub-authors">Online, European Digital Media Observatory</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-meta"><p class="pub-year">2023</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MEDIA -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section__label">In the media</p>
      <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        My research on institutional design and polarisation has been featured in Belgian media including 
        <em>Knack</em>, <em>Het Laatste Nieuws</em>, <em>RTBF</em>, and <em>Bruzz</em>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- INVITE ME -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section__label">Invite me</p>
      <div style="max-width: 680px; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 6px;">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Available for lectures, debates, and workshops</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          I am available for guest lectures, panel discussions, workshops, and public debates on topics related to 
          polarisation, democratic resilience, political conflict, and the state of democracy in Belgium and Europe.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          I speak to a wide range of audiences: secondary school students, university classes, local governments, 
          civil society organisations, media professionals, and the general public.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.75;">
          Interested? Get in touch at <a href="mailto:kamil.bernaerts@vub.be">kamil.bernaerts@vub.be</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
